Pre-heat your #oven{} to 120 degrees. Boil a large #pot{} of water with @salt{1/4%tsp} for your pasta. Slice the @cherry tomatoes{1} in half lengthways. Very finely chop as much @red chilli{1/2} as you dare.

Strip the @lemon thyme{3} leaves by pinching the stalks and running your fingers along them. Toss the tomatoes in the thyme leaves and a pinch of salt and @pepper{} for seasoning. Place them on a #baking tray{} in the oven for ~{20%minutes} until shrivelled and sweet.

Chop the very top and bottom from the @courgette{1} and slice in half lengthways. Slice each half lengthways into five more strips and then chop widthways into 1cm cubes. Peel and very finely chop the @garlic clove{1}.

Place the @walnuts{2.5} in a clean #tea towel{} and whack them gently with a #saucepan{} to break them up slightly.

When the tomatoes are 10 mins from ready toss the @fettuccine{200%g} in the pot of boiling water. Cook the pasta until 'al dente' (i.e. cooked through but with a slight bit of firmness left). Before you drain the pasta keep 1/2 cup of the starchy pasta water.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot add the chilli, courgettes, garlic and @capers{1} with a pinch of salt and cook for ~{5%minutes}. Meanwhile finely chop the @black olives{1} (remove any stones). Add in the walnuts and olives and cook for ~{1%minute} before moving to the next step.

Grate in 1/2 tsp of @lemon{1/2}(zested) zest (more if you like) and pour in the 1/2 cup of pasta water. As it begins to bubble tip in your pasta, the cherry tomatoes and the @hard Italian style cheese{2}(grated). Toss everything together and drizzle over 2 tsp of @lemon juice{2%tsp} before serving.

> For tonight's Quick Dish we're whisking you away to the coast of Amalfi in the south of Italy, for something zingy and refreshing.

> The trick to this recipe is to keep back half a cup of your pasta water just before you drain the pasta and this'll help you create a silky sauce to go with your fettuccine.